[[File:Bicolor flag of Tamil Eelam.svg|thumb|Flag of the Tamil Democrats with the traditional colors of Tamil Eelam ]] '''Global Tamil Forum'''(GTF) is an International [[Tamil people|Tamil]] organization meant to further Tamil causes in Tamil areas of Sri Lanka <ref>[http://www.globaltamilforum.org/gtf/content/about-gtf About GTF]</ref> GTF supports [[self-determination]] for Tamils and wants [[Justice]] for [[War crime]]s against Tamils. It is headed by [[S. J. Emmanuel]]. In UK it works with both [[Labour Party (UK)|Labour]] and [[Conservative Party (UK)|Conservative]] Parties .<ref>[http://www.timesonline.co.uk/tol/news/world/asia/article7038481.ece Miliband risks Sri Lanka’s wrath to support Global Tamil Forum]</ref> It consists of Tamil organizations across the world and to create a united Tamil voice.<ref>[http://www.tamilnet.com/art.html?catid=13&artid=29840 Grass root organisations form Global Tamil Forum]</ref>
