'''Juan Manuel Guillén Benavides''' (born November 24, 1941) is a [[Peruvian]] [[philosopher]] and [[politician]]. In 2007, he became President of the [[Arequipa Region]].

==Biography==
Guillén was born on November 24, 1941 in [[Arequipa]] city. Guillén's initial education was at school Nº9513 and Nº951 followed by the Colegio Nacional Independencia Americana. Between 1960 and 1964, Guillén studied philosophy at the [[National University of St Augustin of Arequipa]] (UNSA), earning a [[Doctor of Philosophy|PhD]]. From 1973 to 1975, Guillén was director of the philosophy program at UNSA.{{sfn |JNE|2006}}

From 1999 to 2002, Guillén was mayor of Arequipa.{{sfn |Arce|2010| p=147}}{{sfn |JNE|2006}} He was credited with leading the 2002 protests against plans to privatize the region's electrical utilities.<ref>http://yaleglobal.yale.edu/content/latin-america-turns-left</ref> Guillén was President of the [[Arequipa region]] from January 2007 through June 2010, and again from October 2010 through December 2014.{{sfn |Cahoon}}

