'''Syed Abdul Sayeed''' is an Indian philosopher and professor of [[philosophy]] at [[The English and Foreign Languages University]]. He has perviously taught in [[Aligarh Muslim University]] for eighteen years. Sayeed received his PhD in 1985 from [[IIT Kanpur]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Eflu professor justifies pay hike, arrears|url=http://www.deccanchronicle.com/131129/news-current-affairs/article/eflu-professor-justifies-pay-hike-arrears|website=[[Deccan Chronicle]]|accessdate=9 July 2017|language=en|date=29 November 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=A Perspective on the Analysis of Knowledge|url=http://www.unipune.ac.in/snc/cssh/ipq/english/IPQ/26-30%20volumes/26-4/26-4-4.pdf|website=[[Indian Philosophical Quarterly]]|accessdate=9 July 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Why the intellectual is the heart of democracy|url=http://fountainink.in/?p=8265|website=[[Fountain Ink Magazine]]|accessdate=9 July 2017|date=26 May 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|last1=Sayeed|first1=Syed A.|title=Interdisciplinary Perspectives in Political Theory|date=2011|publisher=SAGE Publications India Pvt Ltd|pages=151–170|url=http://sk.sagepub.com/books/interdisciplinary-perspectives-in-political-theory/n8.xml|chapter=Dismantling the Political1}}</ref>
